             FIXED DECIMAL


    In FIXED DECIMAL NOTATION, a
    number is displayed with any
    number of decimal places you
    desire.  Eight decimal places
    is the maximum number that
    you can use.  To set the 
    number of places, enter the
    number you want, then hit the
    T key.  When in FIXED DECIMAL
    NOTATION, FIX appears on the
    left side of the screen. See
    F S E on how to convert from
    FIXED DECIMAL, SCIENTIFIC,
    and ENGINEERING NOTATION.
